- The following values for fluid properties are assigned to achieve Ra=10e9:

--> Rho     = 1.225 
--> g       = 0.022353 (so Beta can be 1.0)
--> Lambda  = 0.000037425576
--> Delta_T = 39 
--> mu      = 1.789e-5 
--> Cp      = 1.0 specific heat (heat capacity)
--> Beta    = 1.0 (Volume expansion coefficient) - Thermal Exp. Coeff.

alpha = lambda / (rho * Cp)
nu    = mu / rho 
L     == Characteristic length (height of the cavity here = 0.7) 
Ra    = g* Beta / (nu * alpha) * Delta_T * L^3


